 Should psychotherapy be used in tandem with drugs? How does one choose among group, individual, or family therapy? What are the benefits and drawbacks of drugs such as Prozac? Of beta blockers? Of tranquilizers? Are psychiatric problems passed on to one's children? What are the merits of acupuncture, hypnosis, meditation, sex therapy?From the complexities of schizophrenia and obsessive-compulsive disorder to the delicate practicalities of sexual response, this guide offers all that a woman might want to know about protecting her psychological health.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aWomenxMental health. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh1 aEisenstat M.D., Stephanie A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aZiporyn Ph.D., Terra, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674270923?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674270923423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674270923/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles